# ============================================================================
# _iggy — zsh completion for **iggy** — apache/iggy, the **Apache Iggy
#            persistent message-streaming platform** — an Apache
#            Software Foundation top-level project (Iggy moved to the
#            ASF in early 2025 from the iggy-rs/ org, joining Apache
#            Kafka + Apache Pulsar + Apache RocketMQ as a top-tier
#            ASF-blessed broker, and is one of the very small number
#            of ASF projects written entirely in Rust).  Iggy is
#            positioned as the **Kafka alternative for the
#            cloud-native + low-latency + low-memory + multi-
#            transport era**:  supports **QUIC + TCP + HTTP**
#            transport protocols simultaneously (the same broker
#            binary speaks all three);  capable of millions of
#            messages per second per node;  the typed
#            persistent log is stored as append-only segment files
#            with mmap'd indexes (the same architectural pattern
#            Kafka pioneered + LinkedIn open-sourced in 2011);
#            replicated via Raft (the typed `iggy-consensus`
#            workspace member);  multi-tenant via the typed
#            Stream/Topic/Partition/Segment/Message hierarchy.
#            Native QUIC transport via the canonical pure-Rust
#            QUIC 1 implementation **quinn**, enabling sub-
#            millisecond connection setup + 0-RTT resumption +
#            multi-stream multiplexing without TCP head-of-line
#            blocking.  Rust=183 **OPENS** Axis 128 (pure-Rust
#            IETF QUIC 1 transport protocol / **quinn** ecosystem —
#            `quinn` + `quinn-proto` + `quinn-udp` + `quinn-tls` +
#            `h3-quinn` + the typed `Endpoint` + `Connection` +
#            `RecvStream` + `SendStream` + `Datagrams` primitives)
#            at 1/0/0.
