# WHAT IT IS
#   Iggy is the **Apache message-streaming broker** — modeled
#   architecturally on Apache Kafka + Apache Pulsar but written
#   from scratch in Rust with first-class multi-transport
#   support and an order-of-magnitude smaller memory footprint
#   per broker node.  Use cases:
#
#     • **Kafka-style log-as-a-service**       persistent
#       append-only topic-partition logs with consumer-group
#       offset tracking
#     • **Pulsar-style multi-tenant streaming**  hierarchical
#       Stream/Topic/Partition namespace with per-stream RBAC
#     • **NATS JetStream alternative**         for use cases
#       that need persistent streams + lightweight pub/sub
#     • **Redis Streams alternative**          for higher-
#       throughput persistent log workloads
#     • **AWS Kinesis alternative**            self-hosted
#       streaming without AWS account dependency
#     • **Confluent Cloud alternative**        self-hosted
#       Kafka-API-compatible (Iggy bridge layer exists)
#
#   The `iggy` CLI is the operator + developer entry point for
#   the broker — analogous to `kafka-topics.sh` +
#   `kafka-console-producer.sh` + `kafka-console-consumer.sh` +
#   `kafka-consumer-groups.sh` + `kafka-storage.sh` + the AWS
#   `aws kinesis` CLI rolled into one tool.
#
#   Subcommand surface (clap-derive Subcommand enum;  many
#   subcommands have short aliases for ergonomic interactive
#   use):
#
#     Stream + topic + partition + segment hierarchy:
#       • iggy stream (s) {create|delete|update|get|list|purge}
#       • iggy topic (t) {create|delete|update|get|list|purge}
#       • iggy partition (p) {create|delete}
#       • iggy segment (seg) {delete}
#
#     Message I/O:
#       • iggy message (m) {send|poll|flush}
#
#     Server inspection + management:
#       • iggy ping                              broker liveness
#                                                + round-trip
#                                                time
#       • iggy me                                current client
#                                                info
#       • iggy stats                             broker
#                                                statistics
#       • iggy snapshot                          collect
#                                                troubleshooting
#                                                data bundle
#
#     Auth + authorization:
#       • iggy user (u) {create|delete|update|get|list|change-
#                        password|permissions|set-status}
#       • iggy pat {create|delete|list}          personal access
#                                                tokens
#
#     Client + cluster + consumer-group + consumer-offset:
#       • iggy client (c) {get|list}             connected
#                                                clients
#       • iggy cluster (cl) metadata             cluster topology
