# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `apache/iggy`'s workspace `Cargo.toml` declares the typed
#   workspace `[workspace.dependencies] quinn = "..."` entry,
#   and `core/sdk/Cargo.toml` consumes it via the typed
#   `quinn = { workspace = true }` directive.  The
#   `core/sdk/src/quic/` module implements the typed
#   `IggyClient::with_quic_transport()` constructor, using
#   typed `quinn::Endpoint::client(local_addr)` /  typed
#   `endpoint.connect(server_addr, server_name)` /  typed
#   `connection.open_bi()` /  typed `connection.open_uni()` /
#   typed `connection.read_datagram()` /  typed
#   `connection.send_datagram()` primitives.  Server side at
#   `core/server/src/server/transport/quic/` uses typed
#   `quinn::Endpoint::server(server_config, bind_addr)` +
#   typed `endpoint.accept()` loop pattern.
#
#   **quinn** (`quinn` crate;  GitHub org `quinn-rs/quinn`) is
#   **THE canonical pure-Rust IETF QUIC 1 implementation** —
#   Benjamin Saunders + Dirkjan Ochtman + the quinn-rs
#   community's reference pure-Rust implementation of the
#   IETF QUIC protocol stack (RFC 8999 invariants + RFC 9000
#   QUIC v1 + RFC 9001 TLS-on-QUIC + RFC 9002 loss detection
#   + RFC 9221 unreliable datagrams + RFC 9287 greasing +
#   RFC 9308 deployment + RFC 9368 v1-to-vN compatibility +
#   draft-ietf-quic-ack-frequency + draft-ietf-quic-bdp-frame).
#   In active development since 2017, with 4,300+ ★ on
#   github.com/quinn-rs/quinn.  Funded primarily by individual
#   sponsors + Cloudflare Research (Cloudflare adopted quinn
#   internally for some QUIC tooling pre-Cloudflare's own
#   quiche implementation) + the Mozilla Open Source Support
#   awards from 2018 onward.
#
#   quinn ships:
#
#     • Typed `quinn::Endpoint`        typed `Endpoint::client`
#                                      / `Endpoint::server` /
#                                      `Endpoint::accept` /
#                                      `Endpoint::connect` /
#                                      `Endpoint::rebind` /
#                                      `Endpoint::set_default_client_config`
#                                      / `Endpoint::set_server_config`
#                                      / `Endpoint::local_addr`
#                                      typed lifecycle
#     • Typed `quinn::Connection`      typed `open_bi` /
#                                      `open_uni` /
#                                      `accept_bi` /
#                                      `accept_uni` /
#                                      `read_datagram` /
#                                      `send_datagram` /
#                                      `close` /
#                                      `closed` /
#                                      `remote_address` /
#                                      `stats` / `rtt`
#     • Typed `quinn::SendStream`      typed
#                                      `write_all_chunks` /
#                                      `write_chunk` /
#                                      `finish` / `reset` /
#                                      `id` / `set_priority`
#                                      stream-output operations
#     • Typed `quinn::RecvStream`      typed
#                                      `read_chunk` /
#                                      `read_chunks` /
#                                      `read_to_end` / `stop`
#                                      stream-input operations
#     • Typed `quinn::Incoming`        typed accept-handshake
#                                      negotiation
#     • Typed `quinn::Connecting`      typed in-flight connect
#                                      future with typed
#                                      `into_0rtt` + typed
#                                      `handshake_data`
#                                      accessors
#     • Typed `quinn::ClientConfig`    typed builder with typed
#                                      crypto provider, typed
#                                      transport config, typed
#                                      retry policy, typed
#                                      initial-RTT estimation
#     • Typed `quinn::ServerConfig`    typed cert-resolver,
#                                      typed crypto, typed
#                                      transport-config-by-
#                                      peer-address
#     • Typed `quinn::TransportConfig` typed knobs: typed
#                                      `max_idle_timeout` /
#                                      `max_concurrent_bidi_streams`
#                                      / `max_concurrent_uni_streams`
#                                      / `stream_receive_window`
#                                      / `receive_window` /
#                                      `send_window` /
#                                      `keep_alive_interval` /
#                                      `congestion_controller_factory`
#                                      / `mtu_discovery_config`
#                                      / `enable_segmentation_offload`
#                                      / `initial_rtt` /
#                                      `initial_mtu` /
#                                      `min_mtu` /
#                                      `persistent_congestion_threshold`
#                                      / `enable_ack_frequency`
#     • Typed congestion controllers   typed concrete:
#                                      `NewReno`, `Cubic`,
#                                      `Bbr` (BBR v1)
#     • Typed crypto provider          typed `quinn-tls`
#                                      (rustls-backed) is the
#                                      default;  typed
#                                      `quinn-plaintext`
#                                      (no encryption — for
#                                      benchmarking + intra-
#                                      cluster traffic) is
#                                      pluggable
#     • Typed 0-RTT resumption         typed
#                                      `quinn::ZeroRttAccepted`
#                                      with typed
#                                      `accept_0rtt` /
#                                      `into_0rtt`
#                                      transitions
#     • Typed retry token + stateless
#       reset
#     • Typed datagram (DG) frames     RFC 9221 unreliable
#                                      datagrams typed
#                                      `Datagrams` accessor
#     • Typed connection migration     typed `Connection::
#                                      rebind` for connection
#                                      ID + path migration
#                                      (the QUIC "phone moves
#                                      from wifi to LTE
#                                      without dropping the
#                                      connection" feature)
#     • Typed connection-ID rotation   typed CID-set management
#                                      for typed multi-path
#                                      + privacy
#     • Typed MTU discovery            typed DPLPMTUD
#                                      implementation
#                                      (RFC 8899) for typed
#                                      path MTU probing
#     • Typed packet pacing            typed sender pacer
#                                      for congestion control
#                                      + AQM compatibility
#     • Typed segmentation offload     typed UDP GSO+GRO
#                                      with typed
#                                      `quinn-udp` socket
#                                      wrapper
#     • Typed `h3-quinn`               typed HTTP/3 adapter
#                                      (the typed
#                                      `h3` crate's
#                                      transport-trait
#                                      implementation backed
#                                      by quinn) — the path
#                                      every HTTP/3 client +
#                                      server in Rust uses
#     • Typed `quinn-proto`            typed sans-IO state
#                                      machine (the typed
#                                      raw protocol state
#                                      machine that quinn
#                                      itself drives with
#                                      tokio;  also usable
#                                      stand-alone with a
#                                      custom async runtime)
#     • Typed runtime abstraction      typed `quinn::Runtime`
#                                      trait with concrete
#                                      typed `TokioRuntime`,
#                                      `AsyncStdRuntime`
#                                      shipped implementations
#                                      + typed user-provided
#                                      custom runtimes
#
#   quinn is the QUIC library behind essentially every modern
#   Rust QUIC/HTTP3 application:
#
#     • **Deno** (denoland/deno, 100,000+ ★) — quinn for the
#       typed `Deno.serveHttp` HTTP/3 server side + typed
#       `fetch` HTTP/3 client side
#     • **AWS s2n-quic alternative**     quinn is the
#       community-led peer (AWS s2n-quic is the AWS-funded
#       Rust QUIC stack;  quinn is the broader-community
#       leader by adoption)
#     • **Cloudflare quiche alternative**  quiche is
#       Cloudflare's Rust QUIC (but it's primarily Cloudflare-
#       internal-driven);  quinn is the cross-org community
#       leader
#     • **reqwest** (seanmonstar/reqwest, 9,000+ ★) — typed
#       HTTP/3 support via h3 + quinn (with typed
#       `--features http3`)
#     • **Veloren** (the open-source MMORPG, 3,000+ ★) — quinn
#       for the typed game-client/server transport
#     • **Ambient game engine** — quinn for the typed
#       networked game-state replication
#     • **EasyTier** — peer-to-peer VPN mesh
#     • **atm0s-media-server** — the typed Rust media server
#     • **rmqtt** — typed Rust MQTT broker with typed QUIC
#       MQTTv5-over-QUIC support
#     • **Apache Iggy** (this very project)
#     • **lapdev** — the typed Coder-alternative remote-dev
#       platform (covered as `_lapdev-cli`)
#     • **Hyperledger Iroha** — typed enterprise blockchain
#       transport
#     • **8xff/atm0s-media-server** — typed P2P media routing
#     • **videocall-rs** — typed Rust+WebTransport video
#       conferencing
#     • **muDCN** — typed Named-Data-Networking transport
#     • Plus hundreds of internal Rust services + IoT +
#       embedded HTTP/3 stacks + game-server transports.
#
#   The quinn project is structurally significant because it
#   was the **first mature production-grade Rust IETF QUIC 1
#   implementation** — pre-quinn, Rust QUIC tooling was
#   either:
#     (a) wrapping Google's quiche-the-C++-Chromium-internal
#         library via FFI (no longer viable after Google
#         deprecated it in favor of MASQUE),
#     (b) wrapping ngtcp2 (the C QUIC reference) via FFI
#         (defeats single-binary Rust deployment),
#     (c) toy implementations that hadn't passed the IETF
#         QUIC interop tests.
#   quinn was the first that **passed every IETF QUIC interop
#   test** + was widely deployed in production by major Rust
#   shops (Deno, Cloudflare's research arm, reqwest, Apache
#   Iggy).
#
#   Verified via:
#     gh api repos/apache/iggy/contents/core/sdk/Cargo.toml
#       → [package] name = "iggy"
#       → quinn = { workspace = true }  (workspace-pinned
#                                        direct dep)
#     gh api repos/apache/iggy/contents/core/cli/Cargo.toml
#       → [package] name = "iggy-cli"
#       → [[bin]] name = "iggy"
#     raw.githubusercontent.com apache/iggy main
#         core/cli/src/main.rs
#       → use clap::Parser;
#       → use crate::args::{ Command, IggyConsoleArgs,
